\begin{document}
\begin{sfragment}[id=sec.course-contents]{Course Contents}
\usemodule{wisski/slides/nutshell?WissKI-nutshell}
\usemodule[courses/Jacobs/GenCS/course]{www/slides?html}
\usemodule[courses/Jacobs/GenCS/course]{www/slides?CSS}
\usemodule{progintro/slides?proglang-synsem}
\usemodule[smglom/computing]{mod?persistent}
\usemodule[smglom/db]{mod?ERD}

\begin{sparagraph}
The course comprises two parts that are given as two-hour/week lectures.
\end{sparagraph}

\begin{sparagraph}[title=IWGS 1 (the first semester)]
begins with an introduction to \sn{programming} in \python which we will
use as the main computational tool in the course; see
\sref[file=progintro/sec/progintro.en]{sec.progintro} and
\sref[file=progintro/sec/datastructures.en]{sec.datastructures}. In particular we will
cover
\begin{itemize}
\item systematics and culture of \sn{programming}
\item program and \sns{control structure}
\item basic \sns{data structure} like numbers and strings, in particular
character encodings, Unicode, and regular expressions.
\end{itemize}
Building on this, we will cover
\begin{enumerate}
\item digital documents and document processing, in particular; text files, markup
systems, \sn{html?HTML}, and \sn{xml?XML}; see \sref[fallback=Chapter
4,file=digdocs/sec/digdocs.en]{sec.digdocs}.
\item basic concepts of the \sr{WWW}{World Wide Web}; see \sref[fallback=Chapter
5,file=webapps/sec/www-basics.en]{sec.www-basics}
\item Web technologies for \sn{interactive} documents and applications; in
particular \sn{internet} infrastructure, web browsers and servers, PHP, dynamic
\sn{html?HTML}, JavaScript, and \sn{CSS?CSS}; see \sref[fallback=Chapter
5,file=webapps/sec/webapps.en]{sec.webapps}.
\end{enumerate}
\end{sparagraph}

\begin{sparagraph}[title=IWGS 2 (the second semester)]
\usemodule[smglom/www]{mod?semantic-web}
\usemodule[smglom/computing]{mod?image-processing}
covers selected topics and exemplary tools that will become useful in the DH. We will
cover
\begin{enumerate}
\item \Sns{database}; in particular \sr{ERD}{entity relationship diagrams}, CRUD
operations, and \sn[post=ing]{query}; see
\sref[file=databases/sec/databases.en]{sec.databases}.
\item \Sn{image processing} tools, see \sref[fallback=Chapter
9,file=images/sec/images.en]{sec.image-processing}
\item Using the ontologies and the \sn{semantic web} for Cultural Heritage; see
\sref[fallback=Chapter 11,file=semweb/sec/ch-ontologies.en]{sec.ch-ontologies}
\item The \sn{WissKI-nutshell?WissKI} System: A Virtual Research Environment for
Cultural Heritage; see \sref[fallback=Chapter
12,file=wisski/sec/wisski.en]{sec.wisski}
\item Copyright and Data Privacy as legal foundations of DH tools; see
\sref[fallback=Chapter 10,file=legal/sec/legal.en]{sec.legal}
\end{enumerate}
\end{sparagraph}

\begin{sparagraph}[title=Idea]
\usemodule[smglom/www]{mod?webapp}
The first semester lays the foundations by introducing \sn{programming} in
\python and work our way towards \sns{web application}, which form
the base of most modern tools in the DH. In
\sref[file=booksapp/sec/books-app.en]{sec.books-app}, we pull all parts together to
build a first, simple web application with \sn{persistent} storage that manages a
set of books.

After an excursion into project management systems, we introduce methods and tools for
their management. Here, we extend our \sn{web application} to deal with \sr{digital
image}{image} fragments; actually building a simple replacement for a prominent DH
\sn{web application}.

Finally, after another excursion -- this time into the legal foundations of intellectual
property and data privacy the course culminates in an introduction of the \sn{WissKI-nutshell?WissKI}
system, a virtual research environment for documenting cultural heritage artifacts.
Indeed the \sn{WissKI-nutshell?WissKI} system combines all topics in the course so far.
\end{sparagraph}
\end{sfragment}
\end{document}

